Razer has launched its Power Bank accessory, a 12,800mAh portable battery which can power smartphones and laptops. The device features a single USB Type-C and two USB Type-A ports, and can provide power to a laptop powered by a USB Type-C port. Users can also charge their smartphones with the unit. Razer said the Power Bank can increase the battery life of its Blade Stealth Ultrabook by up to six hours. Razerâ€™s Power Bank uses Qualcomm Quick Charge 3.0 and Apple fast charge to recharge four-times faster than conventional charging products. The device will be available from March 2017, priced at $150.   